// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance SwingAngleEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Measures the swinging motion of the hoist in the lab-scale gantry crane for trajectory accuracy."
    DTDFVocab:producedData SwingAngleData
]

instance Anemometer : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Quantifies wind speed affecting the gantry crane's hoist movement for trajectory validation."
    DTDFVocab:producedData WindSpeedData
]

instance CranePositionSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Captures real-time kinematic states (joint angles, velocities, accelerations) of the gantry crane's movable components."
    DTDFVocab:producedData CraneStateData
]

instance ControllerSignalSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Logs controller signals and operational commands transmitted to the gantry crane's actuators."
    DTDFVocab:producedData ControllerSignalData
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Interaction
instance SwingAngleData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom SwingAngleEncoder
]

instance WindSpeedData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom Anemometer
]

instance CraneStateData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom CranePositionSensor
]

instance ControllerSignalData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom ControllerSignalSensor
]

instance CombinedCraneData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom CraneStateData, ControllerSignalData
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance KinematicModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "CAD-based kinematic model of the gantry crane created in Autodesk Fusion 360 for trajectory simulation and validation."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo Fusion360Enabler, GantryLibEnabler
]

instance TrajectorySimulationModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Behavioral model for simulating crane trajectories and validating against physical execution."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo GantryLibEnabler
]

instance OperationalData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Time-series historical data of crane operations including kinematic states, trajectory execution metrics, and controller logs."
    DTDFVocab:fromData CombinedCraneData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo TimescaleDBEnabler, GrafanaEnabler
]

instance RealTimeCraneState : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Continuously updated real-time state data of the gantry crane for synchronization with the digital twin."
    DTDFVocab:fromData CraneStateData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo MQTTBrokerEnabler, ContinuousValidationService
]

// C11: Enablers
instance Fusion360Enabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Autodesk Fusion 360 used for creating and maintaining the crane's CAD and kinematic models."
    DTDFVocab:enables KinematicModelService
]

instance GantryLibEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Custom Python module (gantrylib) for data processing, control logic, and digital twin services."
    DTDFVocab:enables OptimalControlService, ContinuousValidationService, DataVisualizationService
]

instance DockerEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Containerization tool ensuring reproducibility and portability of the digital twin environment."
    DTDFVocab:enables DeploymentService
]

instance TimescaleDBEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Time-series database storing historical operational data with SQL-like querying capabilities."
    DTDFVocab:enables HistoricalDataLoggingService, DataVisualizationService
]

instance GrafanaEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Hosts the real-time dashboard for monitoring crane metrics and operational insights."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataVisualizationService
]

instance MQTTBrokerEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Eclipse Mosquitto (MQTT) broker facilitating bidirectional data streaming between physical crane and digital twin."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataTransmissionService, ContinuousValidationService
]

// C6: Services
instance KinematicModelService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service for managing and validating the kinematic model of the gantry crane."
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneStateVisualizationInsight
]

instance OptimalControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Implements real-time control algorithms to optimize crane operations (e.g., trajectory planning, energy efficiency)."
    DTDFVocab:provides OptimalTrajectoryInsight, EnergyEfficiencyAction
]

instance HistoricalDataLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Stores time-series operational data for longitudinal analysis of crane behavior."
    DTDFVocab:provides OperationalTrendInsight
]

instance DataVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Delivers Grafana dashboard for real-time monitoring of crane metrics and Python-based front-end for interactive exploration."
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneStateVisualizationInsight
]

instance ContinuousValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Employs distance metrics and threshold-based validation to compare physical and digital system states for synchronization and anomaly detection."
    DTDFVocab:provides SystemSynchronizationInsight, FaultDetectionAction
]

instance DataTransmissionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Facilitates low-latency, event-driven updates between physical crane and digital twin via MQTT."
    DTDFVocab:provides DataStreamingInsight
]

instance DeploymentService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Ensures reproducible and portable deployment of the digital twin environment using Docker."
    DTDFVocab:provides EnvironmentReproducibilityInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance OptimalTrajectoryInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time insights into optimal crane trajectories for efficient material handling."
]

instance EnergyEfficiencyAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automatically adjusts crane operations to minimize energy consumption."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance OperationalTrendInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Longitudinal analysis of crane operational patterns and performance metrics."
]

instance CraneStateVisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time visualization of crane kinematic states (position, velocity, system health) via Grafana dashboard."
]

instance SystemSynchronizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Continuous validation of physical-digital system synchronization through distance metrics."
]

instance FaultDetectionAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Detects anomalies in crane operation by comparing physical and digital twin states."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance DataStreamingInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Monitoring of bidirectional data flow between physical crane and digital twin via MQTT."
]

instance EnvironmentReproducibilityInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Ensures consistent deployment of the digital twin across different environments using Docker."
]

// C2: Acting Components
instance CartMotorController : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Controls horizontal movement of the gantry crane's cart via embedded controller interface."
]

instance HoistMotorController : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Manages vertical hoisting movement and payload manipulation via electromagnet integration."
]

instance CraneElectromagnet : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "End-of-hoist electromagnet for manipulating small pucks representing containers in the lab-scale setup."
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control flows from the digital twin to the physical gantry crane are executed via the **Control Application**, a Python-based system that interfaces with the **Physical Crane Interface**. Commands include trajectory generation (e.g., optimal movement paths without residual swinging) and operational directives (e.g., puck placement). The **Trajectory Generator Service** produces kinematically optimized trajectories, which are validated by the **Simulation Service** before execution. Control messages are transmitted via the **MQTT Broker**, with formats unspecified but assumed to align with the crane's controller protocols. Validation and authentication mechanisms are not explicitly described, though the **Continuous Validation Service** implies real-time comparison of executed trajectories against simulations to detect deviations. Feedback systems include operator notifications via the **Dashboard** (Grafana) when thresholds are breached. Conflict resolution and command execution confirmation are not detailed, but the system’s design suggests a closed-loop architecture where deviations trigger alerts."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system exhibits asynchronous temporal synchronization in the GreenhouseDT exemplar, where virtual machine images are preloaded with prerecorded data, suggesting offline or batch-based validation rather than real-time updates. The Air Quality Management exemplar supports three distinct temporal applications: **runtime visualization** (real-time or near-real-time monitoring), **simulation** (time-accelerated or deterministic modeling), and **prediction** (forward-looking forecasting with unspecified granularity). The Gantry Crane system implies continuous validation and real-time status updates, though no explicit synchronization frequency or latency requirements are documented. No explicit mention of temporal granularity (e.g., millisecond, second, minute) or service-specific time scales (e.g., sensor polling rates) is provided in the documents."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin systems in the documents adopt a **lightweight, ad-hoc orchestration approach** rather than relying on commercial frameworks. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplifies a **self-adaptive digital twin** with **behavioral adaptation** for both the physical greenhouse and its digital counterpart, coordinated via **InfluxDB (time-series database)** and **ActiveMQ (message broker)**. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar uses **Microsoft Azure tools** for pipeline implementation, integrating **AutomationML** for model-driven engineering and **Raspberry Pi-based sensors** for real-time data ingestion. Both exemplars emphasize **containerization/virtualization** (e.g., virtual machine images, Docker-like dissemination) to ensure **modularity and reproducibility**. The **gantry crane** system, though not detailed in orchestration, aligns with this pattern by leveraging **C4 Model architecture** for **context and container-level coordination**, suggesting a **cyber-physical system (CPS)-centric constellation** with **loosely coupled components**. No explicit **resource management policies** (e.g., QoS, priority scheduling) or **federated twin architectures** are described."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "
The **lab-scale gantry crane** employs a **Continuous Validation Service** that **continuously compares measurements of executed trajectories** (e.g., motor positions, swing angles) with simulations. This service calculates **distance metrics** between real and simulated trajectories and compares the result against an **acceptable threshold** to detect deviations. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar implies **dynamic fidelity adjustments** via self-adaptive behavioral models, while the **Air Quality Management** system likely supports **cloud-based validation** through Microsoft Azure tools. Quality assurance processes for the gantry crane are architecture-driven, leveraging the **C4 Model** for consistency checks, though explicit uncertainty quantification or error correction mechanisms are not detailed.
"
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The digital twin’s technical network infrastructure relies on a **service-oriented architecture** with the **MQTT Broker** as the central communication hub for inter-service signaling. The **TimescaleDB database** stores all system-generated data, while the **Dashboard (Grafana)** visualizes real-time metrics. Network topology is not explicitly defined, but the use of MQTT suggests a lightweight, publish-subscribe model suitable for edge deployments. Bandwidth and latency requirements are not quantified, though continuous validation implies low-latency constraints for trajectory comparison. Reliability and redundancy mechanisms are not described, but the system’s ability to operate without the digital twin hints at offline-capable components. Security protocols are unspecified, though the use of a dedicated broker and centralized database may imply basic access controls."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The digital twin system is deployed entirely on a **personal computer**, with all six containers (e.g., **TimescaleDB**, **Grafana Dashboard**, **Trajectory Generator Service**) running locally. Computational requirements are inferred to support real-time trajectory generation, simulation, and validation, though specific CPU/GPU or memory constraints are not provided. Storage demands are met by **TimescaleDB**, optimized for time-series data. Scalability mechanisms are not addressed, as the system is tailored for a lab-scale gantry crane with no mention of distributed deployment. Availability and reliability are assured by the crane's ability to operate autonomously without the digital twin, though no explicit failover or backup strategies are documented."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system demonstrates **limited, domain-specific horizontal integration**. The GreenhouseDT exemplar integrates with **InfluxDB** (time-series database) and **ActiveMQ** (message broker) for internal data exchange, with no external system dependencies documented. The Air Quality Management exemplar relies on **AutomationML** (a standardized engineering data format) for Digital Twin modeling and **Microsoft Azure tools** for cloud-based pipeline execution, implying interoperability with **construction engineering tools** (e.g., CAD/BIM software) but without explicit protocol details. The Gantry Crane system lacks documented external integrations, though the broader context suggests potential alignment with **logistics or cyber-physical systems (CPS) frameworks**. No ERP, IoT platform, or cross-Digital Twin federation protocols (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT) are mentioned."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The only explicitly mentioned **standardization effort** is the use of **AutomationML** in the Air Quality Management exemplar for digital twin modeling. No other industry standards (e.g., IEC 62714, ASHRAE 62.1, ISO 16890, or FAO standards), certification frameworks, or interoperability protocols (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT) are referenced in the provided documents. The ad-hoc nature of the implementations precludes adherence to formal compliance frameworks."
]